  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to better understand how individuals make decisions regarding the
      meals they order. Participants' ordering decisions at lunchtime at a chain restaurant will be
      recorded over several weeks to study ordering habits over time. Lunch menus will be provided
      by the study, and the menu format will vary the way in which information on caloric content
      is displayed.

      The impact of different labeling formats on total calories in the chosen meal will be
      assessed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
